ProductTitle: Ultra Rare LOUIS VUITTON Tote Luggage Keepall Steamer Carry on Duffle Bag Luxury

ProductTitle: Antique! Three (3) Original Chinese Ming Dynasty Paintings & Calligraphy
ProductDescription: *** A lot of three (3) Ming Dynasty paintings & calligraphy. The artwork is signed by Chen Yi (1469-1538). These pieces of art could be in collaboration with Chen Yi's best friends: Wen Zhengming(1470-1559), Shen Zhou(1427-1509), Xu Lin( 1462-1548). The above artists were best friends in a literati and influential group. **** Three Chinese Ming dynasty scroll paintings with calligraphy.  Each painting depicts a landscape with birds, trees, and flowers accompanied by calligraphy. It was common during the Ming Dynasty to include calligraphy poems with paintings. It was not unusual for scholar to add the poetry for a well known painter. The paintings measures approximately 46 X 13in(Image29X9.5), 47X13in(Image29X9.5), and 42X13in(Image29X9.5). These are amazing paintings from the Ming Dynasty. It would be fantastic to frame them and hang them to display their beauty and charm. I also recommend adding  matting to enhance the colors and cover the worn edges.  What a great opportunity to add these pieces to your existing collection or start a new collection.

ProductDescription: Hand-Painted Hanging ScrollTitle: Landscape*About the calligraphy, we try to write what we have deciphered as much as possible. If it is not written, it means that it could not be deciphered. We can translate the deciphered calligraphy to English. But, if it is a poem or in Chinese, it cannot be translated.Artist: Ueda Kokei was a Shijo-school painter and the first son of Ueda Kocho (1788-1850).Size: 168 x 125.5 cmCondition: Normal *Considering the time, it was made. (stains)[Special Items] Coming Under the Spotlight - Osaka Gadan (Painting School)We, En Corporation, an antique dealer based in Osaka has been vigorously collecting the works of painters active in Osaka during the modern and early modern periods, known as "Osaka Gadan (Osaka painting circles)".During the Edo period, Osaka was lined with storehouses belonging to feudal lords from various regions and functioned as a distribution hub. It was thriving as a town for merchants and townspeople. As industrialization progressed after the Meiji era (1868-1912), Osaka became the center of industry, and a rich culture and arts flourished.Some characteristics of Osaka Gadan are:Bunjin-ga (or literati painting): Literati artists like Kimura Kenkado or Okada Beisanjin were active beside their professions as townspeople.Realistic painting followed Maruyama-Shijo School: Nishiyama Hoen and Kan'ei, Fukada Chokujo, Niwayama Koen are famous.Outstanding activities of women painters: Hoshika Yukino, Becchaku Tsukino, Hashimoto Hanano and Shii Hoshino are famous. They studied under Kitano Tsunetomi, known as the father of bijin-ga of Osaka Gadan. Shima Seien is also a charismatic figure selected for the Bunten Exhibition at the young age of 20.In recent years, Osaka Gadan has been re-evaluated around the world. Some of recent exhibitions held in Japan are:"Salon Culture and the Pictorial Arts of Kyoto and Osaka" (The National Museum of Modern Art, Kyoto 2022)"Japanese Paintings of Modern Osaka" (Nakanoshima Museum of Art, Osaka 2023)"Osaka in the Eyes of Women Painters" (Nakanoshima Museum of Art, Osaka 2023-2024)In April this year, we also held an exhibition titled "The Beautiful World of Artists in Osaka - Pursued in Taisho Period- (2024)" with the cooperation of Seki Kazuo, a big collector of Osaka Gadan artists. The exhibition included works that had been missing for many years and were welcomed as new discoveries.This item is the one introduced at the exhibition.We hope you can find the excitement directed towards Osaka Gadan.*We do our best in writing the description and judging paintings. ProductTitle: Antique Oil Painting by Leighton 48"Ã—39 â€œLuther Williams was a mayor of Macon GA
ProductDescription: Antique Oil Painting by Leighton “Luther Williams was a mayor of Macon GA. Williams was originally born in South Wales. His mother had connections to John Adams’ presidency, and his father was a clergyman for the Church of England. When he was 14 years old, he began providing for himself and became employed in the civil service commission of the British government, according to information at the Washington Memorial Library archives. Four years later, Williams moved to Macon after being hired by the Western Union Telegraph Company where he worked from 1873-1880. After that, he devoted himself to the city’s economic growth running his own Bank and Trust Company and building one of the strongest financial centers in the region. Williams’s love for athletics was what helped bring baseball and the stadium to Macon. During a city council meeting, he was asked to step out as council members discussed naming the stadium in his honor.
